ET
BT
/F0 10 Tf
0 0 0 rg
28.346 747.798 Td
(Windows XP can be told to "boot" any directory or file location. For example, the Recovery Console is saved in) Tj
ET
BT
/F0 10 Tf
0 0 0 rg
28.346 733.625 Td
(the cmdcons directory. In the cmdcons directory is a 512-byte file named bootsect.dat. Windows XP will treat a) Tj
